Problem Statement

Bob is playing a game called "Some Help".
In this game, there are N soldiers, where N is an even number. There are also N treasure chests, each with a bonus value given by the array Bonus.
The power of each soldier is described by an array A of size N. For each i, the power of the ith soldier is an integer between 1 and N/2, and each number between 1 and N/2 occurs exactly twice in A.

The game has N rounds and each round proceeds as follows for the i-th player:
1. Find the first player on their right (index R > i) whose power is a multiple of the power of the ith player (A[R] % A[i] == 0).
2. If no such player R is found, do nothing.
3. If such a player R is found, Bob can choose a chest in the range [i, R] that gives the maximum bonus.
4. The total XP is initially zero and for each successful round it is increased by this maximum bonus.

Find the total XP that Bob can obtain from all N rounds.

Constraints
1 <= N <= 10^5
1 <= A[i] <= 10^5
1 <= Bonus[i] <= 10^5

